The '''Antigua and Barbuda national rugby union team''' represents [[Antigua and Barbuda]] in the sport of [[rugby union]]. They have thus far not qualified for a [[Rugby World Cup]], and have not participated in qualifying tournaments.

Antigua and Barbuda compete  in the [[Caribbean Championship]], a tournament which includes [[Trinidad and Tobago national rugby union team|Trinidad and Tobago]], [[Bermuda national rugby union team|Bermuda]], the [[Cayman Islands national rugby union team|Cayman Islands]], [[Jamaica national rugby union team|Jamaica]], the [[Bahamas national rugby union team|Bahamas]], [[British Virgin Islands national rugby union team|British Virgin Islands]], and [[Guyana national rugby union team|Guyana]].<ref name=Completerugby>Bath, Richard (ed.) ''The Complete Book of Rugby'' (Seven Oaks Ltd, 1997 {{ISBN|1-86200-013-1}}) p78</ref>

