The '''Grotenburg-Stadion''' is a multi-use [[stadium]] in [[Krefeld]], [[Germany]]. It is used mostly for [[Association football|football]] matches and hosts the home matches of [[KFC Uerdingen 05]]. The stadium has a capacity of 34,500 and was built in 1927.
