{{infobox country at games | NPC = IRQ | NPCname = Iraqi National Paralympic Committee | games = Paralympics | year = | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = | location = | competitors = | sports = | flagbearer = | rank = | gold = 3 | silver = 6 | bronze = 4 | officials = | appearances = | app_begin_year = | app_end_year = | summerappearances = {{Team appearances list|team=Iraq|competition=Summer Paralympics|begin_year=1992|end_year= }} | winterappearances = | seealso = }} '''[[Iraq]]''' made its [[Paralympic Games]] début at the [[1992 Summer Paralympics]] in [[Barcelona]]. It has competed in every edition of the Summer Paralympics since then, but never in the Winter Paralympics. Iraqi Paralympians have won a total of thirteen medals: three gold, six silver and four bronze.<ref>[http://www.paralympic.org/Sport/Results/search.html?npc=IRQ&gender=all&medal=all&sport=all&games=all Iraq at the Paralympics], [[International Paralympic Committee]]</ref>
