{{Infobox Golf Facility |golf_facility_name = North Oaks Golf Club |image = |imagesize = |caption = |location = [[North Oaks, Minnesota]] |establishment = 1950 |type = Private |owner = <!-- name of organization/company --> |operator = <!-- name of organization/company --> |holes = 18 |tournaments = MN Section [[PGA Championship]] in 1954 and 2000 |website = [http://www.northoaksgolfclub.com/viewCustomPage.aspx?id=1 northoaksgolfclub.com] |course1 = <!-- individual course name, can leave blank if same as article title--> |designer1 = [[Stanley Thompson]] |par1 = 71 |length1 = {{convert|6700|yd}}<ref name="Morgan1952">{{cite news|last=Morgan|first=G|title=Anniversary Issue|newspaper=The Oak Leaf|date=August 1952}}</ref> |rating1 = |slope1 = |record1 = |course2 = <!-- if only one course: leave this entry and all below parts blank --> |designer2 = |par2 = |length2 = |rating2 = |slope2 = |record2 = }}
'''North Oaks Golf Club''' (NOGC) is located in [[North Oaks, Minnesota]], United States. The championship [[golf course]] was originally designed by [[golf course architect]] [[Stanley Thompson]] in 1950. The course is located just inside the private community of North Oaks. It has hosted numerous MGA Championships and a few MN section [[PGA Championship]]s in 1954 and 2000.
==History== In 1883 [[James J. Hill]], known to be '''The Empire Builder''', purchased a 3,070-acre piece of land from [[Charles D. Gilfillan]]. This piece of land Hill named the North Oaks Farm. When Hill passed on, his son, [[Louis W. Hill]] inherited much of the land. From here the Hill heirs took over and maintained the land. <ref>{{cite book|last=O'Malley Elfstrom|first=Kate|title=North Oaks Golf Club|year=1999|publisher=North Oaks Golf Club, Inc|location=North Oaks, MN|page=4-5}}</ref> Fast forwarding to 1950, more land was bought and the planning process began. [[Stanley Thompson]] began work on designing the course. It officially opened in the summer 1951. Shortly before it had opened, a “hurricane” hit. The storm caused two holes to be flooded. <ref name="Morgan1952" /> North Oaks Golf Club became an official private golf club in 1953. The term and process called a [[shotgun start]], was first used at North Oaks Golf Club. Although it was incorrectly credited three years later to a course in Washington.<ref>{{cite book|last=O'Malley Elfstrom|first=Kate|title=North Oaks Golf Club|year=1999|publisher=North Oaks Golf Club, Inc|location=North Oaks, MN|page=20}}</ref> Fast-forwarding even more to the year 2007, Lehman Design Group renovated the course. They fixed particular issues while mostly sticking to Thompson’s original design. <ref>{{cite web|title=North Oaks Golf Club Course Renovation|url=http://www.duininckgolf.com/news/north-oaks-golf-club-course-renovation/|publisher=Duininck Golf|accessdate=March 15, 2013}}</ref>
