'''The Golf Club at Harbor Shores''' is a [[country club|golf club]] located in [[Benton Harbor, Michigan]], part of the Harbor Shores development on [[Lake Michigan]].

==History==
All 18 holes of the course were opened on July 1, 2010.<ref>"[http://www.harborshoresgolf.com/layout10.asp?id=213&page=6653 Welcome to Harbor Shores, Home of the 2012 and 2014 Senior PGA Championship] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110110014408/http://www.harborshoresgolf.com/layout10.asp?id=213&page=6653 |date=2011-01-10 }}". ''The Golf Club at Harbor Shores'' official website.</ref> The course held its Grand Opening on July 10, 2010, with [[Johnny Miller]], [[Arnold Palmer]], [[Tom Watson (golfer)|Tom Watson]], and its designer, Jack Nicklaus, in attendance.<ref>{{cite news |first=Julie |last=Swidwa |format= |coauthors= |title='A great day' |url=http://www.theh-p.com/articles/2010/08/11/local_news/1703906.txt |work=[[The Herald-Palladium]] |publisher= |date=2010-08-11 |accessdate=2010-08-18 }}</ref>

===Controversy===

Local residents have taken exception to the golf course using a portion of the public [[Jean Klock Park]] for three of its holes. The Michigan Surpreme Court ruled in favor of Harbor Shores to keep the three holes at Jean Klock Park.<ref>"[http://www.harborshoresgolf.com/layout10.asp?id=213&page=6816&newsId=236 Harbor Shores Is Cleared by Courts for Full Operations] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101006103133/http://harborshoresgolf.com/layout10.asp?id=213&page=6816&newsId=236 |date=2010-10-06 }}" (press release). ''The Golf Club at Harbor Shores'' official website, 2010-02-08.</ref><ref>{{cite news |first=Darren |last=Phllips |format= |coauthors= |title=Darren Phllips: Harbor Shores gaining welcome publicity |url=http://www.theh-p.com/articles/2010/08/18/sports/1756333.txt |work=[[The Herald-Palladium]] |publisher= |date=2010-08-18 |accessdate=2010-08-18 }}</ref>

==Tournaments==
[[File:The Golf Club at Harbor Shores.jpg|thumb|256px|right|Hole no. 7 at Harbor Shores]]
Harbor Shores hosted the [[Senior PGA Championship]] in 2012, 2014, 2016, and 2018 and is scheduled to host the tournament in 2020, 2022, and 2024.<ref>{{cite news |first=Angelo |last=Di Carlo |title=Senior PGA Championship Returning to Benton Harbor in 2014, 2016 and 2018 |url=http://www.wndu.com/home/headlines/Senior-PGA-Championship-returning-to-Benton-Harbor-in-2014-2016-and-2018-217016161.html |publisher=[[WNDU-TV]] |date=2013-07-25 |accessdate=2013-07-26 }}</ref>

